  "body": "<!-- CURSOR_SUMMARY -->\n> [!NOTE]\n> **Medium Risk**\n> Changes a default in RL training that can affect numerical stability and memory/perf characteristics across runs; adds only a warning-based guardrail for small values rather than enforcing a hard constraint.\n> \n> **Overview**\n> Updates RL training to auto-set `model.fused_lm_head_chunk_size` from 2048 to 8192 (and updates the changelog/documentation string accordingly).\n> \n> Adds validation that warns when an explicitly configured chunk size is below 8192 (while still enforcing a hard minimum of 512), to flag potentially unstable configurations.\n> \n> <sup>Written by [Cursor Bugbot](https://cursor.com/dashboard?tab=bugbot) for commit 7b9ab3d4b94b88ad9bebe0d3096c8a013c9b22fd. This will update automatically on new commits. Configure [here](https://cursor.com/dashboard?tab=bugbot).</sup>\n<!-- /CURSOR_SUMMARY -->",
